sentence: The Home Depot, Inc.HD has successfully completed its previously announced acquisition of Interline Brands, Inc. for $1.625 billion.
The company had inked the deal to buy Interline Brands in July.
This acquisition will help Home Depot to better serve its Pro customers.
Jacksonville, FL-based Interline is a distributor and direct marketer of broad-line maintenance, repair and operations (MRO) products.
Previously, Interline, a leading name in its field, was jointly owned by Goldman Sachs Capital Partners, P2 Capital Partners, LLC and management.
As per sources, Home Depot, the world's largest home improvement retailer, derives nearly 35% of its annual revenues through the Pro services business.
Improving housing markets have enabled homeowners to take up big ticket home improvement projects, which in turn, have boosted the Pro services business' performance.
Going forward, the markets are expected to continue to recover.
Hence, the acquisition of Interline will help Home Depot to make the most of this situation.
Interline boasts of strong outside sales force and fulfillment capabilities in the housing MRO market.
Plus, it has an impressive distribution network of over 90 locations across the U.S., Canada and Puerto Rico.
Interline is one of biggest buyouts of the company in a decade.
Also, Home Depot has promoted Bill Lennie, who currently serves as the president of Canada operations, to the post of Executive Vice President, Outside Sales and Service.
In his new post, Lennie will oversee Pro, installation and the MRO services business which also includes the acquired Interline Brands.
At present, Home Depot carries a Zacks Rank #2 (Buy).
Other favorably ranked stocks in the related industry are Tempur Sealy International Inc. TPX , Restoration Hardware Holdings Inc. RH and Fortune Brands Home & Security, Inc. FBHS .
While Tempur Sealy International holds a Zacks Tank #1 (Strong Buy), Restoration Hardware and Fortune Brands Home & Security carry a Zacks Rank #2.
